===Etymology===
"To pass over" > "to offend against, oppose". Compare {{zh-l|*氾}}.

This character originally had bilabial nasal (*-''m'') final in Old and Middle Chinese, but had undergone [[dissimilation]] (from bilabial plosive *''b''-) to become *-''n'' in most dialects. However, there are still some dialects that retain this feature, such as Meixian and Teochew dialect. Similar dissimilation happened in {{zh-l|*帆}}.

